abstract: Striking deep behind enemy lines, the Ukrainians are depleting Russias combat potential, slowing its advance in the east and creating new vulnerabilities in the south.
snippet: Striking deep behind enemy lines, the Ukrainians are depleting Russias combat potential, slowing its advance in the east and creating new vulnerabilities in the south.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine  From spring into summer, the Ukrainian military was pummeled by Russian artillery in eastern Ukraine, steadily losing ground and as many as 200 soldiers a day in a mismatched, head-to-head contest. But in recent weeks, Ukraine has shifted its strategy with the help of new weaponry and succeeded, at least for now, in slowing Russias advances.
